asset().details: returns collateral vault asset (which is the token of another lending protocol, like an aToken, eToken, etc.)

balanceOf(address).details: balanceOf(address(this)) is used by intermediate vault to check the collateral amount. This vault borrows from intermediate vault using the vault as the collateral asset. This means balanceOf(borrower-from-intermediate-vault's-perspective) needs to return the amount of collateral held by borrower-from-intermediate-vault's-perspective. On first deposit, this value is the deposit amount. Over time, it decreases due to our siphoning mechanism. Thus, we return borrower owned collateral.

borrow(uint256,address).details: This function calls the internal _borrow function to handle the protocol-specific borrow logic, then transfers the target asset from the vault to _receiver.

params._receiver: The receiver of the borrowed assets
params._targetAmount: The amount of target asset to borrow

canLiquidate().details: calling canLiquidate() in other functions directly causes a read-only reentrancy issue, so move the logic to an internal function.

canRebalance().details: Excess credit exists when the relationship between borrower collateral and reserved credit becomes unbalancedThe calculation varies depending on the external protocol integration

returns._0: uint The amount of excess credit that can be released, denominated in the collateral asset

checkVaultStatus().details: This function is called after any action that may affect the vault's state.Executed as a result of requiring vault status check on the EVC.

params.assets: address of tokens for which reward is to be claimed

collateralForBorrower(uint256,uint256).details: Uses Twyne's dynamic liquidation incentive model (whitepaper eq 7.1):   - Borrower receives: C * [1 - _t - i(_t)] where _t = B/C (Twyne LTV)   - i(_t) is the dynamic liquidation incentive that varies based on health Three regimes based on borrower's LTV (_t = B/C): 1. _t >= ^max_t (severely unhealthy): i = 1 - _t     Borrower gets: C * [1 - _t - (1 - _t)] = 0    All remaining equity goes to liquidator as maximum incentive 2. _t <= _safe * _e (healthy, no CLP reservation needed): i = 0     Borrower gets: C * [1 - _t - 0] = C - B    No liquidation incentive; borrower keeps full equity 3. _safe * _e < _t < ^max_t (intermediate): linear interpolation    i = (1 - ^max_t) * (_t - _safe * _e) / (^max_t - _safe * _e)     Borrower gets: C * (1 - _safe * _e) * (^max_t - _t) / (^max_t - _safe * _e)    Incentive grows linearly from 0 to (1 - ^max_t) as LTV increases

params.B: debt in common unit of account (like USD)
params.C: user collateral in common unit of account (like USD)

params._evc: address of EVC deployed by Twyne

convertToAssets(uint256).details: This is used by intermediate vault to price the collateral (aka collateral vault). Since CollateralVault.balanceOf(address(this)) [=shares] returns the amount of asset owned by the borrower, collateral vault token is 1:1 with asset.

params.__asset: address of vault asset (AaveV3AToken wrapper shares)
params.__categoryId: Category ID for e-mode on Aave

isExternallyLiquidated().details: External liquidation occurs when the external lending protocol (e.g., Euler) directly liquidates collateral from this vaultDetects liquidation by comparing the tracked totalAssetsDepositedOrReserved with the actual token balance - if actual balance is less, external liquidation has occurred

returns._0: bool True if the vault has been externally liquidated, false otherwise

liquidate().details: Liquidation needs to be done in a batch.Liquidation uses dynamic liquidation incentive model:   1. Liquidator must first transfer collateral to the borrower as compensation.   2. The liquidator then becomes the new borrower of this vault.   3. Liquidator is responsible to make the position healthy before the batch ends.   4. Liquidator may wind down the position and keep remaining collateral as profit.The liquidator's profit comes from the difference between the collateral they   receive (by becoming the vault owner) and the compensation paid to the borrower.

maxRelease().details: This represents the total debt (principal + accumulated interest) owed by this vault to the intermediate vault from which credit was reservedIn the protocol mechanics, this corresponds to C_LP (credit from LPs) in the mathematical formulationThe value is denominated in the collateral asset

returns._0: uint The maximum amount of collateral asset that can be released back to the intermediate vault

rebalance().details: Excess credit exists when: liqLTV_twyne * C < safety_buffer * liqLTV_external * (C + C_LP)Anyone can call this function to rebalance a position

params.assets: Amount of collateral asset to withdraw.

repay(uint256).details: If _amount is set to type(uint).max, the entire debt will be repaidThis function transfers the target asset from the caller to the vault, then calls the internal _repay function to handle the protocol-specific repayment logicReverts if attempting to repay more than the current debt

params._amount: The amount of target asset to repay, or type(uint).max for full repayment
